The R package `BestNextStudy` brings a friendly syntax to study

- how well have extant studies collectively contributed to our understanding of the focal association being studied in a meta-analysis at a given point in time
- how has our understanding of the focal association being studied in a meta-analysis evolved over time
- what should be the optimal next study to further our understanding of the focal association being studied in a meta-analysis

The [application](Application_CS_Retention.html) page demonstrates the use of `BestNextStudy` package to understand the association between Customer Satisfaction and Retention using sample data included in the package.

The package is available on [GitHub](https://github.com/bestnextstudy/bestnextstudy){target="_blank"}  and can be installed to your local computer by running the following lines of code.

```{r echo=FALSE, include=TRUE}
library(knitr)
opts_chunk$set(tidy.opts=list(width.cutoff=60),tidy=TRUE)
```

```{r klippy, echo=FALSE, include=TRUE}
klippy::klippy()
```

```{r load_packages , warning=FALSE , message = FALSE, class.source='klippy'}

# Installing `devtools` package if not alredy installed
if(!require(devtools)){
    install.packages("devtools")
    library(devtools)
}

#Installing `bestnextstudy` package
devtools::install_github("bestnextstudy/bestnextstudy")
library(bestnextstudy)
```


